reviews.text:
I am leaving this review shortly after leaving this place so as to give an accurate description of my experience here. I am hoping the owner sees this and works on it ASAP, as it is terribly detrimental to his/her establishment.
So to start, the service here was abysmal. I visited this restaurant with my wife, and we sat close to the bar. We ordered our food and drinks and waited to be served. After about 25 minutes our drinks came, and we were chatting while awaiting our food. After 20 minutes of nursing our cocktails we just decided to order another round of drinks because the wait was getting longer(it had been 45 minutes at this point). So our second round came after about 15 minutes and we sipped on those as well because we didn‚Äôt want to ruin our appetite before our meal arrived.
Now this were things got bad, and my frustration grew. I previously failed to mention earlier that all this while we were seated close to the bar, all the employees at work in the afternoon of 23/05/23 were dancing, some grinding and recording what I presumed to be tiktok videos, also making cocktails for themselves while gossiping about guests at the establishment which we overheard as we were very close to them. I mean how do you do this??? We could clearly tell from their behavior that it was something they were used to doing, which indicated a lack of supervision on whoever is managing the place. After about an hour and a half of waiting I called the waitress who took our order to inquire as to the status of our food and she told us they were now going to start ours as they had just served a couple that came before us(the only other people there). So I informed her to cancel our order if they were now going to start ours after all this while, and she told us she was going to check on it, only for her to return 2 minutes later with our food which was getting cold. The thing was, she didn‚Äôt even know the status of our food as she was busy partying with her workmates and our question was if we didn‚Äôt follow up or tell her to cancel the order we would have sat there till one of them realized they were not on a vacation but at work. This was absolutely terrible and unpardonable.
To the owner, if you ever happen to read this and have security cameras. Just review footage from 23/05/23 b/n 4pm to 6pm and you‚Äôll be amazed. I almost considered taking videos to show but decided to spare myself the hustle.
Needless to say I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll be revisiting anytime soon.

reviews.text:
My partner and I have been thinking about a getaway for a couple of weeks now. We had been torn between Western Region and Volta Region, so many awesome places to see either ways. More so, due to work commitments it was proving a bit of a challenge to get away so when this loooong Easter weekend presented itself, we just had to take advantage.

Let's just say that whatever our expectations for Afrikiko were paled in comparison to our actual experience!

The drive to the resort was a pretty good one (if you're traveling from Accra that is) Besides the bit of traffic along the Afienya - Shai Hills Road it was generally okay. Our drive back took us barely 2 hours (from Afrikiko to 37 Military Hospital). Definitely 4/5!
First impression of the Resort was good. We drove on a narrow cemented road from the main road down to the entrance of the facility. I must mention that getting there in the evening (0630pm) did add to the ambience too with the whole place lit up.

If you're a nature person it'll feel like you're in heaven for sure!

Food was good throughout our stay. Service takes a while though but I can say in all honesty that it wasn't unreasonable.

They had quite a number of fun activities at the resort - boat rides, live band, salsa dancing, painting lessons...

There was a variety of birds within the premises too, that's if birdwatching is your thing..üòÉ
The staff were very pleasant throughout our stay too!

Overall we had a good time! Would definitely visit Afrikiko again..‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê!

reviews.text:
Hill Palace was dealt a good hand as they have one of the most iconic views of the Akuapem mountain road and excellent flora all around them. You can see the beauty of Accra and Ayi Mensah area at night which is breathing.  They can easily accommodate about 100 people as they have many rooms, conference rooms, camping spots, and a good bar.
Went there with the family for the holidays and was excited to see a calm but less pricy location. Bed and breakfast with a family-size room of around 500 cedis which was the highest-rated room,  there were even easier-on-the-pocket options like 250 cedis, 300 cedis, and 400 cedis, all rooms come with complimentary breakfast,  water, and swimming pool, and the view.
We planned on staying longer but our trip was disturbed by giant mosquitoes in the rooms. We thought about the safety of the kids and moved away. It is close to the government Peduase lodge and security is good but the mosquitoes were worst.
All in all, a good place and affordable.
